      "tests": [
        {
          "id": "noon_summer_eq",
          "description": "Reference scenario: cos_sza=0.9174 (pinned from t_unix=1782043200 s, lat=0.0\u00b0, lon=0.0\u00b0), T=298.0 K, P=101325 Pa, H2O=450.0 ppb. Compares the migrated component's 13 J-rates and 2 spot-checked F_i fluxes against the upstream GasChem.jl FastJX_interpolation_troposphere reference computed at the same conditions (see scripts/migrations/extract_fastjx_data.jl).\n\nTolerance rationale (rel=5e-3 / abs=1e-15): FastJX J-rates are returned from interpolated lookup tables; 5e-3 absorbs differences between Julia (upstream FastJX_interpolation_troposphere) and Python (lambdify) interpolation kernels on the cross-section / quantum-yield grids \u2014 interpolation roundoff dominates the negligible ODE truncation since tspan=[0,1] s. abs=1e-15 floors the dark-sibling scenarios where every J-rate is exactly 0.",
          "parameter_overrides": {
            "T": 298.0,
            "P": 101325.0,
            "H2O": 450.0,
            "cos_sza": 0.9173780810128263
          },
          "time_span": {
            "start": 0.0,
            "end": 1.0
          },
          "tolerance": {
            "rel": 0.005,
            "abs": 1e-15
          },
          "assertions": [
            {
              "variable": "j_O3",
              "time": 0.0,
              "expected": 0.00035414030106515254
            },
            {
              "variable": "j_O31D",
              "time": 0.0,
              "expected": 3.365088599120879e-05
            },
            {
              "variable": "j_o32OH",
              "time": 0.0,
              "expected": 9.261009485267697e-11
            },
            {
