            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "morning_midlat",
          "description": "Reference scenario: cos_sza=-0.3004 (pinned from t_unix=1782032400 s, lat=40.0\u00b0, lon=-97.0\u00b0), T=298.0 K, P=101325 Pa, H2O=450.0 ppb. Compares the migrated component's 13 J-rates and 2 spot-checked F_i fluxes against the upstream GasChem.jl FastJX_interpolation_troposphere reference computed at the same conditions (see scripts/migrations/extract_fastjx_data.jl).\n\nTolerance rationale (rel=5e-3 / abs=1e-15): cos_sza is negative (sun below horizon) so all J-rates are 0 \u2014 abs=1e-15 is the operative floor; rel=5e-3 mirrors the daytime test for consistency.",
