        },
        {
          "id": "T_sweep",
          "description": "Temperature sensitivity of the photolysis rates at fixed actinic flux (cos_sza=0.917, noon summer equator). Sweeps T from 240 K (cold UT) to 310 K (warm BL) at default P=101325 Pa, H2O=450 ppb. j_NO2 is largely T-insensitive (σ_NO2 has no T dependence in this binning), while j_O(1D) carries the strong ϕ_O(1D)(T) quantum-yield temperature dependence and the σ_O3(T) cross-section adjustment — making j_O31D the canonical T-sensitive J-rate.",
